properties.name: Calle 26
properties.description: Posted by Jennpants 3825 W. 26th St., Chicago, IllinoisLa Villita in Chicago was one of the best places I have ever passed through. Music on every block, good food, lots of things to see. It\'s likely the locals here will feel more comfortable speaking Spanish, so brush up on your language skills gringo!

properties.name: Clejani, Romania
properties.description: Posted by JennpantsI want to go here soooo badly. It is the home of Taraf de Haidouks among other amazing bands, orkestars, and musicians. A town known for its music -- it\'s sent numerous locals abroad on tour. I want to go and soak in the music, find someone to tutor me in the finer points of accordion playing....

properties.name: Highway clusterfuck
properties.description: Posted by JennpantsSan Jose, CaliforniaHave you ever tried hitchhiking out of the San Jose area? I wouldn\'t suggest it. Got dropped off here from some friendly driver from Santa Cruz. Anytime I would step foot onto the highway some "friendly" highway policeman would march back off the road. When I finally did get a ride it was only to their weird compound because they thought I was waiting on the side of the highway for work...to they put me to work in their weird car lot/junk yard/backyard sorting scrap metal until they walked away and then I ran away.

properties.name: Hinkle = Bad Place to Get Pulled Off of a Train
properties.description: Posted by JennpantsHinkle, OregonThe plan was to ride to trampfest happening several summers ago. We were going to take a route through the middle of the country because, why not? It would be fun. One of my co-riders was anxious as soon as we got out of Portland...the car we were in was too sketchy, we weren\'t far enough back, etc. So when we pulled into a siding in Hinkle he informed us that rideable wasn\'t more than 20 cars behind us. Off we went. 10 cars, 20 cars, 30 cars...."Hey, where was this rideable again?" "Oh, I think its at the end of the line." (Liar) In the middle of the summer, in the middle of nowhere, with giant packs on the last thing you want to be doing is running like mad over train ballast for a rideable that might not actually exist before your train leaves you behind. Well, we got spotted by a train cop and were all cited tickets. We hitchiked to Pasco, Washington (also a poor place to hop trains, by the by...)

properties.name: I don't speak French, he didn't speak Spanish or English
properties.description: Posted by JennpantsLille, FranceI was hitchhiking from England to Spain. Straight off the ferry from Dover I realized something crucial: I don\'t speak French. Somehow, for some reason, the first person that picked me up took me to Lille. Beautiful highway signs in France. Yup.

properties.name: Iceland
properties.description: Posted by JennpantsIt\'s an island: one highway follows the entire circumference. Glaciers, natural hot springs, icy tundras, weird-ass musicians? What more does anyone need?

properties.name: Jump off the Train!
properties.description: Posted by Jennpants Berwyn, IllinoisRiding piggyback overnight from LaCrosse, Wisconsin my traveling friends and I woke up to ChicagoLand. We knew we had to get off soon -- it was broad daylight and there was *gasp* a cop shadowing the train. We threw our bags off the train and then ourselves. Laughing at the silly looks we received from all the commuters waiting for the next Metra we joined in waiting as well. My companions started making coffee with a rocket stove and some jackass thought it was a bomb and called the cops on us. The cops came, ran our names, and then let us get on the arriving Metra. Welcome to Chicago?

properties.name: Lima, Peru
properties.description: Posted by Jennpants Lima, PeruA big city. One sprained ankle, a bag case of Atahualpa\'s Revenge (read: diarrhea), one anarchist friend, one hell of a time.

properties.name: Machala
properties.description: Posted by Jennpants Banana Capital of the World. Great food. A vibrant border town next to Peru.

properties.name: Mistaken for a baby
properties.description: Posted by Jennpants Continuing an epic hitchhiking journey home this is where someone called the cops on me claiming my hoodie was a baby. The cop that came was as confused as I was. No one wanted to pick us up after that.

properties.name: More Gardens
properties.description: Posted by Jennpants   376 East 162nd Street, #2, Bronx, New YorkAnd amazing groups doing good work in the Bronx. Volunteer for a couple of hours next time you\'re in NYC, you won\'t regret it!

properties.name: Near Death
properties.description: Posted by Jennpants Trying, in vain, to hitchhike home. Night fell, no real places to hide and sleep. While crossing a bridge a driver (drunk? asleep?) heading in the opposite direction swerved in the road and hit the bridge barrier cascading sparks over my head. Five feet (?) closer and it would have been me. I got a hotel room that night.

properties.name: Quito, Ecuador
properties.description: Posted by Jennpants Quito, EcuadorI wish that I had spent much more time here. A true cultural hotspot full of people.

properties.name: Riobamba
properties.description: Posted by Jennpants Riobamba, EcuadorI was only in Riobamba for a few a days, but the surrounding areas are gorgeous.

properties.name: The truckdriver was on crack.
properties.description: Posted by JennpantsRipon, CaliforniaHitchhiking to the bay area, I caught a ride with a fairly friendly driver out of Eugene, Oregon. He was fairly quiet the entire ride and only talked out of the side of his mouth. Come the wee hours, he refused to pull over and drop myself and my traveling partner off claiming that where he was going was, "Good Enough." Ripon, California (the part that I saw anyway) sucks. Slept in an abandoned fireworks shack and then in the morning got a ride with a professional Australian basketball player who took us to SF via Tracy. (Tracy was where he showed us MC Hammer\'s house and we ate apricots.)

properties.name: This was the first time
properties.description: Posted by Jennpants  Alberta Park, Portland, OregonThis was the place where I first told you, "Uh, I think I really like you." You played it cool, but told me later your heart skipped a beat.

properties.name: Tire Blowout!
properties.description: Posted by JennpantsI was two or three days out on a crosscountry drive in a bus converted to run on veggie oil. About 20 miles out from Missoula, Montana our front left tire EXPLODED while on the highway. Several hours and hundreds of dollars later we were towed into town, sold a new tire and ready to go again.

properties.name: Train dead end
properties.description: Posted by Jennpants My train luck from Miami, Florida finally died in Charleston. No trains in sight, a not pedestrian/bum friendly part of town -- If I had known how hard it was going to be to hitchhike I would have stuck around longer. Also: Found the Higgledy Piggledy Headquarters!

properties.name: Tumbes, Peru
properties.description: Posted by Jennpants Tumbes, PeruA beautiful town where amazing public art and drug trafficking intersect.

properties.name: Where some trains go to die
properties.description: Posted by JennpantsLaurel, MontanaOn a highline that suddenly turned into something that wasn\'t the highline, Destination: Laurel, Montana. Interesting place, for the few hours I was there. Hitchhiked to the twin cities.

properties.name: staying in Barcelona
properties.description: Posted by Jennpantstorrassa, Barcelona, SpainWhile traveling through Spain, I spent an amazing week in Barcelona. I almost didn\'t leave.
